sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K952005
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: BBa_J04500 was obtained from the 2012 kit. BBa_K592016 is available in the parts registry, but was obtained directly from the Uppsala-Sweden 2011 team.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This part has the IPTG inducible promoter with ribosome binding site (BBa_J04500) upstream and BBa_K592016 downstream. This will allow for YF1, blue-light sensing protein, and the response regulator, FixJ be promoted when IPTG is present. This can be used in conjunction with FixK2 (BBa_K592006) to selectively express when a cell is exposed to blue-light. This part is available with a constitute promoter in BBa_K952004.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Saimon Sharif

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K592016
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: B0034-YF1-B0034-FixJ, blue light sensor and RR with RBS
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: The components that made up of YF1 fusion protein comes from Bradyrhizobium japonicum and Bacillus subtilis. FixJ comes from the genome of Bradyrhizobium japonicum.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: YF1 works in conjunction with its response regulator, FixJ. This part consists of RBS-coupled YF1 and FixJ without promoter.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: This constructs Strong RBS to ensure good expression.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Lei Sun

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0034
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Varies from -6 to +1 region from original sequence to accomodate BioBricks suffix.

No secondary structures are formed in the given RBS region. Users should check for secondary structures induced in the RBS by upstream and downstream elements in the +50 to -50 region, as such structures will greatly affect the strength of the RBS. Contact info for this part: Brian Chow
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Vinay S Mahajan, Voichita D. Marinescu, Brian Chow, Alexander D Wissner-Gross and Peter Carr IAP, 2003.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: LacI
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: The Plac insert was PCR'd from the MG1655 strain of E.coli K12.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription:
Inverting regulatory region controlled by LacI (BBa_C0010, BBa_C0011, etc.)

The pLac regulatory region is a 243 base-pair sequence with standard BioBrick prefix and suffix sections on its ends. It contains two protein binding sites: CAP, which is generally present in E.coli and is assocciated with cell health and availability of glucose., and LacI, the Lac inhibitor BBa_C0010 which binds in an dimerized cooperative manner to inhibit the transcription of the protein that follows. In the presence of lactose or IPTG, an analog of lactose, LacI is unable to correctly bind and inhibit transcription. This allows BBa_R0010 to be used as a inverter or as a detector of lactose or IPTG.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: LacI binds to this regulator. This part is incompatible with species containing active LacI coding regions. Lactose and IPTG disable the operation of LacI and this regulator. This part is incompatible with environments containing lactose or lactose analogs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: YF1
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance:
Ytva comes from the genome of Bacillus subtilis.
FixL derives from the genome of Bradyrhizobium japonicum.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: YF1 is a fusion protein of YtvA (B.subtilis) and FixL(Br.japonicum). It contains the N-terminal region of YtvA (1-127) and C-terminal region of FixL (258-505), interconnected by a helical linker. This fusion protein is designed by Andreas Moglich and Keith Moffat. As shown in previous research, Illumination of the fusion kinase YF1 reduced net kinase activity by ∼1000-fold in vitro. YF1 also controls gene expression in a light-dependent manner in vivo.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: The sequence information was provided in Moglich and Moffat's article. The physical DNA was synthesized by GenScript. Codon-optimization may enhance its expression.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Lei Sun

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: FixJ
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: FixJ, the response regulator to YF1
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: FixJ comes from the genome of Bradyrhizobium japonicum.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: FixJ comes from the genome of Bradyrhizobium japonicum. It's the wild-type response regulator to YF1, the blue light-sensing fusion protein.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: The sequence was information was provided by Moffat (Moffat et al. 2009). The DNA was synthesized by GenScript.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Lei Sun
